name: I Get a Kick Out of You
comments: There's a film from 1912 called "For His Son" about cocaine addiction, and it had already been around for years when that film was released. It really is much older than most people think.
Always thought he sang the blues more than jazz?

'Shocked to hear a cocaine reference in a song from a man with so many ties to the Mafia?' - Even if true, Frank was well known for not being tolerant of drug use, even by his friends. He broke off his friendship with Sammy Davis, Jr. for several years because he started using cocaine. It's just the original lyric by Cole Porter.
Frank was gonna have one of his private goons rough me up but I talked Rocco out of it..I said,LQQK pal Rocco of mine,I like the song,Frank!
...this sounds a really early version, his voice has developed that beautiful depth......
no one ever could phrase a song like Sinatra...the man was a genius.
This is a true classic by Frank. I love it.
He is all that and more!
Nice little easy listening tune... classic Sinatra, who can say no to that?
Oh my, that trumpet makes me swoon.
